oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Rader Girls School tour group
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a Radner Girls School student group riding a in car while touring New York. Words on the side of the car read "No.5," and "Green car sight-seeing service / B. Way & 23rd St. / Hotel Bartholdi." Radnor Girls School was located on Nolensville Pike in Nashville, and owner Mr. Eshman planned the tour.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
